  fhir:description [ fhir:v "Keys used in the Topography-Morphology data quality check to determine how each morphological family relates to topography. NA (*): the family is accepted with any topography. Plus (+): the family has a restricted set of expected topography sites checked against the MUST list. Minus (-): the family has a restricted set of prohibited topography sites checked against the MUST-NOT list."] ; # 
